 *
 *   CONCRETE coincidence (UTILITY = memoization).  Two quanta with the SAME content-address sha256(verb,a,b)
 *     are the SAME computation on the SAME operands.  The engine indexes (content-address -> witnessed result);
 *     a re-occurrence is RECALLED, not recomputed.  Reuse is sound by construction -- only an EXACT 32-byte
 *     content-address match recalls, so collision-resistance forbids a false reuse.
 *   STRUCTURAL coincidence (INTELLIGENCE = self-map).  Two quanta with the SAME move-SHAPE -- the verb plus
 *     the structural ROLES of its operands (their up/down degree in the web order, operands abstracted away)
 *     -- are the SAME geometric MOVE even across unrelated faculties.  The engine indexes (shape -> the set of
 *     faculties that produced it); a shape seen under >=2 faculties is a CROSS-FACULTY recognition -- III
 *     discovering that two differently-named operations are one move, proven from real traces.
 *
 * AUTONOMY: `coin_fold_web(faculty)` scans the CURRENT isub field once and indexes every quantum -- the whole
 *   mechanism in one deterministic call, self-driven from the eidos fold path + a build-gated KAT; never a CLI
 *   or human or AI in the loop.  SAFETY: the engine owns ONLY its index; it never writes isub/assimilate (it
 *   only reads addresses + the order), so it cannot corrupt the field; bounded (fixed BSS, LOUD-capped, never
 *   crashes when full); deterministic (same field -> same index); tamper-evident (keyed by sha256).
 *   NEVER-A-NUISANCE: O(1) amortised per quantum, silent, no gate that can flake.
